          <div class="post-date">Dec 4, 2024</div>
          <h2 class="post-title">What Technical Product Ownership Really Means</h2>
          <div class="post-content">
            <p>Someone asked me today what makes a "technical" product owner different. My answer: I've been in the trenches. I know what breaking changes feel like at 2 AM. I understand why "just add a feature" isn't simple.</p>
            <p>But more than that - I can translate. I speak engineer and I speak business. I know when to push back and when to compromise. I've earned the trust that comes from understanding both worlds.</p>
            <p>That bridge between business and engineering? That's where I live.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="post-tags">
